# Content Guide: {{ display_name }}

This guide covers everything needed to add and maintain content on this site: frontmatter conventions, image handling, Markdown extensions, SEO metadata, and how to use components inside content.

## Content Structure

Content files live in `src/content/` organised by type:

{% if site_type == "docs" %}
```
src/content/
  docs/
    getting-started/
      index.md           # Section landing page
      installation.md
      configuration.md
    guides/
      ...
    reference/
      ...
```

Documentation pages are nested to reflect the site navigation. Folder names become URL segments. A file named `index.md` becomes the section's root URL.
{% elif site_type == "blog" %}
```
src/content/
  blog/
    2024-01-15-my-first-post.md
    2024-02-03-another-post/
      index.md
      diagram.png       # Co-locate images with the post
  authors/
    jane-smith.md
    john-doe.md
```

Blog posts are named with a date prefix for easy sorting. Co-locate images with the post by using a directory instead of a single file.
{% elif site_type == "landing-page" %}
```
src/content/
  sections/
    hero.md
    features.md
    testimonials.md
    pricing.md
    faq.md
  testimonials/
    customer-a.md
    customer-b.md
```

Landing page sections are Markdown files whose frontmatter drives the section's appearance. The content body is used for longer text (e.g., FAQ answers).
{% elif site_type == "portfolio" %}
```
src/content/
  projects/
    project-slug/
      index.md
      hero.png
      screenshot-1.png
  skills/
    languages.md
    frameworks.md
```

Each project is a directory containing the `index.md` and its associated images. This keeps assets co-located and avoids naming collisions.
{% endif %}

## Frontmatter Reference

### Required Fields (all pages)

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `title` | string | Page title. Used in `<title>`, `<h1>`, and Open Graph. Keep under 60 characters. |
| `description` | string | Short page summary. Used in meta description and Open Graph. 120-160 characters. |

{% if site_type == "docs" %}
### Documentation Page Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Installation"
description: "How to install and set up the project in your local environment."
sidebar:
  order: 2          # Controls position in the sidebar within its section
  label: "Install"  # Short label for the sidebar (defaults to title)
draft: false        # Set to true to hide from the published site
lastModified: "2024-06-01"
---
```

Optional fields:

| Field | Type | Default | Description |
|-------|------|---------|-------------|
| `sidebar.order` | number | 99 | Sort order within the section |
| `sidebar.label` | string | title | Sidebar label (shorter than title) |
| `draft` | boolean | false | Hide from published site |
| `lastModified` | date string | - | Date of last significant update |
| `tableOfContents` | boolean | true | Show the auto-generated TOC |
| `editUrl` | string | auto | Override the "Edit this page" link |

{% elif site_type == "blog" %}
### Blog Post Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "My Post Title"
description: "A summary of what this post covers."
pubDate: "2024-06-15"
author: "jane-smith"      # Must match a file in src/content/authors/
tags:
  - web development
  - performance
draft: false
cover:
  src: "./hero.png"
  alt: "Descriptive alt text for the hero image"
---
```

Optional fields:

| Field | Type | Default | Description |
|-------|------|---------|-------------|
| `pubDate` | date string | required | Publication date (ISO 8601) |
| `author` | string | - | Author slug (references authors collection) |
| `tags` | string[] | [] | Topic tags |
| `draft` | boolean | false | Hide from published site and feeds |
| `cover.src` | string | - | Path to hero image (relative to the post file) |
| `cover.alt` | string | required if cover | Alt text for the hero image |
| `canonicalUrl` | string | auto | Override canonical URL |

